      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable to feel exhausted by the constant effort of trying to fit in and be accepted. But remember, even if you feel like you're just an observer, you still have the power to make a difference in your own life and the lives of others. It's not always about finding a place where you belong, but rather creating your own space where you can be yourself. You don't have to bridge that gap every single day. Take the time you need to rest and recharge. Sometimes, it's okay to just be yourself, even if it feels like you're on a treadmill that never stops. You deserve to take care of yourself, and it's okay to take a break from the effort of trying to fit in. Remember, you are enough just as you are.",
